gineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Compensation</h2><h3>Salary</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=2439478\">Salaries never stay secrets forever. Hiding them only delays the inevitable.</a></li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T16:37:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Politics</h2>","itemHTML":"<li>“Politics is how a middle manager runs interference and creates distractions to make sure you can't see over, around, or through them, and that the people behind them closer to the money can't see you.” (<a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=22808280\">source</a>).</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T16:37:44.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Roles</h2><h3>Engineers</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=11341567\">What makes a Senior Dev</a> - “Time, man. You gotta do your fucking time.”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T15:54:31.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering</h2><h3>Technology</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>“Lots of people make the mistake of thinking there's only two vectors you can go to improve performance, high or wide. High - throw hardware at the problem, on a single machine. Wide - add more machines. <a href=\"https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=8902739\">There's a third direction you can go, I call it <em>going deep</em>.</a>”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T15:21:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"kdeldycke/awesome-engineering-team-management","categoryHTML":"<h2>Engineering</h2><h3>Systems Complexity</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.com/0262014866/?tag=kevideld-20\">Living with Complexity, by Donald A. Norman</a> - In which we learn that, based on <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_of_conservation_of_complexity\">Tesler's law of the conservation of complexity</a>, “the total complexity of a system is a constant: as you make the person's interaction simpler, the hidden complexity behind the scenes increases. Make one part of the system simpler, said Tesler, and the rest of the system gets more complex.”</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T15:12:28.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mgramin/awesome-db-tools","categoryHTML":"<h2>Schema</h2><h3>Changes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/prisma/migrate\">Prisma Migrate</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/prisma/migrate\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">773</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":773,\"repo\":\"prisma/migrate\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Declarative database schema migration tool that uses a declarative data modeling syntax to describe your database schema.</li>","updatedAt":"2020-09-22T12:11:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Components &#x26; Libraries</h2><h4>HTTP Requests</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Scrum/rexios\">rexios</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Scrum/rexios\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;